SEA AREA FORECAST UNTIL 0600 MONDAY 15 DECEMBER 2014
ISSUED AT 0600 SUNDAY 14 DECEMBER 2014
1. GALE WARNING: SOUTHWESTERLY GALES ON IRISH COASTAL WATERS FROM SLYNE
HEAD TO ROSSAN POINT TO BELFAST LOUGH WILL VEER WEST TO NORTHWESTERLY THIS
MORNING .
SMALL CRAFT WARNING: SOUTHWEST TO WEST WINDS WILL REACH FORCE 6 OR HIGHER
FOR A TIME TODAY ON COASTS FROM BELFAST LOUGH TO CARNSORE POINT TO SLYNE
HEAD.
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0300: A STRONG SOUTHWESTERLY AIRFLOW COVERS
IRELAND AS FRONTAL TROUGHS APPROACH FROM THE ATLANTIC. A COLD FRONT WILL
CLEAR SOUTHEASTWARDS DURING TODAY WITH THE FLOW VEERING NORTHWESTERLY AND
BECOMING UNSTABLE.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM SLYNE HEAD TO ROSSAN POINT TO BELFAST LOUGH:-
WIND: SOUTHWEST FORCE 7 OR GALE FORCE 8 AND GUSTY VEERING WEST TO NORTHWESTERLY
LATER THIS MORNING. DECREASING WESTERLY FORCE 6 OR 7 THIS AFTERNOON AND FURTHER
MODERATING FORCE 4 OR 5 TONIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM BELFAST LOUGH TO HOWTH HEAD TO CARNSORE POINT
AND THE IRISH SEA:-
WIND: SOUTHWEST TO SOUTH FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY. WINDS VEERING WEST TO
NORTHWESTERLY THIS AFTERNOON AND DECREASING FORCE 5 OR 6. WINDS DECREASING
FORCE 4 OR 5 TONIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM CARNSORE POINT TO VALENTIA TO SLYNE HEAD-
WIND: SOUTHWEST FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY VEERING WEST TO NORTHWEST LATER
THIS MORNING AND EARLY THIS AFTERNOON AND DECREASING FORCE 5 OR 6. FURTHER
MODERATING WESTERLY FORCE 4 OR 5 EARLY TONIGHT.
WEATHER FOR ALL COASTS AND THE IRISH SEA: RAIN HEAVY AT TIMES. A CLEARANCE
TO SCATTERED SHOWERS WILL FOLLOW FROM THE ATLANTIC LATER THIS MORNING AND
EARLY THIS AFTERNOON.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL COASTS AND THE IRISH SEA POOR TO MODERATE IN PRECIPITATION
OTHERWISE GOOD.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL WILL DEVELOP ON NORTHERN AND WESTERN COASTS
DURING SUNDAY.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 TUESDAY 16 DECEMBER 2014:
MODERATE TO FRESH SOUTHWEST WINDS WILL DECREASE LIGHT TO MODERATE. SHOWERS
BECOMING ISOLATED WITH MAINLY FAIR WEATHER.
